Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} over a medium high heat.

When hot, add the @yellow Thai style paste{45%g} and cook stirring frequently until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Next add the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @soy sauce{12.5%ml}.

Add the @water{100%ml} and bring to the boil.

Pop the @cod fillets{2} into the sauce, making sure it is fully submerged and cook with the lid on, until the fish is cooked, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Trim the @pak choi{1} then thinly slice widthways.

Cut the @sugar snap peas{80%g} into thirds.

Add the bok choy and sugar snap peas to the curry and cook until tender, ~{3%minutes} more.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1/2%bunch}(chopped, stalks and all).

Halve the @lime{1}.

Cook the @steamed basmati rice{1%pack} according to pack instructions.

Taste the curry and squeeze in the lime juice.

Share the rice between your plates.

Top with the cod curry and sprinkle over the @salted peanuts{25%g} and coriander.

Enjoy!